 gray mob once and this happened, or i think..., or this one time...) answer this question:<br>
<br>
If you put enervating poision on your primary weapon, strike somebody with perf, and they live; does the poison con debuff get calculated before the perf damage(which would make perf = perf damage + con debuff ) or after the perf damage (one would negate the other).<br>
<br>
If the poison debuffs after the perf damage, then i am thinking it is leading to a different use, and was never intended to work with high CS anyway.  Could it be that high CS and High poison arent meant to work together at once, similar to how sword and shield, and 2 handed weapons work for tanks.<br>
<br>
Take a look at these 2 rough templates:<br>
<br>
40 stealth<br>
50 CS<br>
36ish weaponskill (maybe like mid 40's with equipment)<br>
15ish dual wield/celtic/LA<br>
11 envenom<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
40 stealth<br>
2 CS<br>
50 envenom<br>
1 weaponskill<br>
50 dual wield(not sure if its possible)<br>
<br>
The first template is a melee heavy assassin, reliant on Critical strike damage to deal major damage, and high weaponskill to finish the opponent off (if they are not one shotted).  This seems to be the current trend also among most assassins.  Enervating (high level) poison has no use to this assassin, his/her envenom skill only adds a slight amount of extra damage or debuffs slightly (or snares).<br>
<br>
The second template is almost the opposite of the first.  This assassin would use thier limited CS ability to land a weak backstab, and using a major con debuff (primary weapon) debuff the opponents hp to a very low level.  Then, the high dual wield would land a poison such as lifebane(?) which does high dot damage and effectively kill the target slowly (who should be too encumbered to pursue the attacker).  This assassin  has no use for high CS damage, or melee skills.<br>
<br>
WHich is more viable? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaaxtherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaax the Rogue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 12:28:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1962.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> odd.</span><hr size=1> I can't see ROGUE B, ever getting to level 50. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Withouth at least a basic Crit Strike, you don't have your bread and butter, Backstab, etc... <br>
Just my 2 cents worth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 12:35:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1962.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: odd.</span><hr size=1> I think the biggest problem with rogue B is the utter lack of weaponskill.  The poisons we have available are not nearly enough to kill something on their own, let alone kill it quickly enough so that it doesn't kill us first.  Without any weaponskill, AND no CS, we're dead pretty soon.  Would a blademaster find it worth it to give up: reinforced armor, weapon spec, AND parry, in return for envenom?  I doubt it would be a smart decision.<br>
<br>
-Caith <p><IMG SRC="http://www.dopplex.net/sigfile2.jpg" ALT="Caith Caidh, 35th Season Nightshade, An Claidheamh Soluis" ALIGN="middle"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usirsameth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirSameth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/02 9:04:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1962.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about this enervating stuff, and random thoughts on pois</span><hr size=1> I would agree with Caith...Rogue B would be seriously gimped in melee combat. An assassin's damage is, supposedly, derived from stealth and critical hits. Mythic gives some good bonus damage on PA, should it work correctly. The other CS styles are the same as all the other weaponskill styles; some good bonuses, but you can't win the fight with them alone.<br>
If you take away a rogue's skill to critical hit, what you have left is a Berzerker. Only you have even less armor  and health and you still can't hit nearly as hard. Poisons are nice when used correctly, but they are not meant to do enough damage to make up for CS skills. <br>
Rogue A seems to me to be the only somewhat viable path to take (although he could trade some CS or stealth for envenom, DW or weaponskill)<br>
<br>
I would like for someone to prove me wrong on this.<br>
<br>
Sameth<br>
